BEGIN_TEXT

Represent the function \( \displaystyle \frac{$a}{(1 - $b x)^2} \) as a power series 
\( \displaystyle f(x) = \sum_{n=0}^\infty c_n x^n \) $BR

\( c_0 = \) \{ans_rule(20)\}  $BR

\( c_1 = \) \{ans_rule(20)\}  $BR

\( c_2 = \) \{ans_rule(20)\}  $BR

\( c_3 = \) \{ans_rule(20)\}  $BR

\( c_4 = \) \{ans_rule(20)\}  $BR

Find the radius of convergence \( R = \) \{ans_rule(20)\}  . $BR

END_TEXT

#@ans=();
$ans0 =  $a ;
$ans1 =  $a*2*$b ;
$ans2 =  $a*3*($b**2);
$ans3 =  $a*4*($b**3);
$ans4 =  $a*5*($b**4);
$ans5 =  $b1;

#&ANS(std_num_cmp_list(@ans) );
